      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): inherit requester model for subagents",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Let native subagent spawns resolve `model: \"inherit\"` from the requester session's active model, including model context passed through `sessions_spawn` and persisted requester session state fallback.\n- Normalize inherited provider/model refs so provider-qualified requester models whose model id also contains `/` are preserved, for example `vllm/openrouter/auto`.\n- Preserve existing model precedence: explicit tool model, per-agent subagent model, default subagent model, target agent model, then global/runtime default.\n- Keep model aliases authoritative, so a configured alias named `inherit` still selects that concrete model instead of the inheritance sentinel.\n- Reject explicit `model: \"inherit\"` for `runtime: \"acp\"` instead of silently omitting the ACP model override; configured native `subagents.model: \"inherit\"` is intentionally not treated as an ACP model override.\n- Update subagent docs/config docs/tool descriptions and focused regression coverage.\n- Supersedes #87628 with a clean replacement branch based on latest `main`.\n\n## Linked context\n\nCloses N/A\n\nRelated #87628\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nNo maintainer request known; this is a replacement for the previous contributor PR.\n\n## Real behavior proof (required for external PRs)\n\nBehavior addressed: Native `sessions_spawn` can explicitly inherit the requester session's active provider-qualified model while preserving existing configured model precedence and alias handling. ACP `model: \"inherit\"` is now rejected explicitly.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS at current head `83a671b64a45c73fc8406f064d58fd5339d7a9c3`, using a temporary isolated Gateway and a local fake OpenAI-compatible `vllm` endpoint. The temporary model ref was `vllm/openrouter/auto` so the provider is qualified and the model id itself contains `/`, matching the slash-preservation case.\n\nExact steps or commands run after this patch:\n\n```console\n$ OPENCLAW_HOME=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof-client \\\n  OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof-client \\\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof.ggFiDJ/openclaw.json \\\n  VLLM_API_KEY=proof-key OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=proof-token \\\n  pnpm openclaw gateway call sessions.patch --json --timeout 10000 --token proof-token \\\n  --params '{\"key\":\"agent:main:main\",\"agentId\":\"main\",\"model\":\"vllm/openrouter/auto\",\"label\":\"Proof parent\"}'\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"entry\": {\n    \"providerOverride\": \"vllm\",\n    \"modelOverride\": \"openrouter/auto\",\n    \"modelOverrideSource\": \"user\"\n  },\n  \"resolved\": {\n    \"modelProvider\": \"vllm\",\n    \"model\": \"openrouter/auto\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThen invoke the real Gateway `tools.invoke` path for `sessions_spawn`:\n\n```console\n$ OPENCLAW_HOME=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof-client \\\n  OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof-client \\\n  OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw-pr-89469-proof.ggFiDJ/openclaw.json \\\n  VLLM_API_KEY=proof-key OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN=proof-token \\\n  pnpm openclaw gateway call tools.invoke --json --timeout 60000 --token proof-token \\\n  --params '{\"name\":\"sessions_spawn\",\"sessionKey\":\"agent:main:main\",\"idempotencyKey\":\"inherit-proof-2\",\"args\":{\"task\":\"Reply exactly PROOF_OK after inheriting the requester model.\",\"model\":\"inherit\",\"cleanup\":\"keep\"}}'\n```\n\nObserved `sessions_spawn` result:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"toolName\": \"sessions_spawn\",\n  \"output\": {\n    \"details\": {\n      \"status\": \"accepted\",\n      \"childSessionKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:2d1d6872-85f3-43d2-bc85-c9edb970e51f\",\n      \"runId\": \"61e78ed7-59a0-4bc5-b6ab-4f6cdb00a31f\",\n      \"mode\": \"run\",\n      \"resolvedModel\": \"vllm/openrouter/auto\",\n      \"resolvedProvider\": \"vllm\",\n      \"modelApplied\": true\n    }\n  },\n  \"source\": \"core\"\n}\n```\n\nChild session store after the Gateway run:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"childKey\": \"agent:main:subagent:2d1d6872-85f3-43d2-bc85-c9edb970e51f\",\n  \"child\": {\n    \"model\": \"openrouter/auto\",\n    \"modelOverride\": \"openrouter/auto\",\n    \"modelOverrideSource\": \"user\",\n    \"modelProvider\": \"vllm\",\n    \"providerOverride\": \"vllm\",\n    \"systemPromptReport\": {\n      \"provider\": \"vllm\",\n      \"model\": \"openrouter/auto\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: `sessions_spawn` returned an accepted child run with `resolvedModel: \"vllm/openrouter/auto\"` and the child session persisted both `modelProvider: \"vllm\"` and `modelOverride: \"openrouter/auto\"`.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live external provider generation with real credentials was not used. The local fake provider was enough to exercise the Gateway, `tools.invoke`, `sessions_spawn`, session patching, and child session persistence paths without touching a real account.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\nWhich commands did you run?\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `node --import tsx scripts/generate-prompt-snapshots.ts --write`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts src/agents/model-selection.test.ts src/agents/subagent-spawn.test.ts src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts`\n- Earlier branch validation retained on this PR: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-selection.test.ts src/agents/openclaw-tools.subagents.sessions-spawn.model.test.ts src/agents/subagent-spawn.test.ts src/agents/tools/sessions-spawn-tool.test.ts src/agents/live-model-dynamic-candidates.test.ts src/agents/acp-spawn.test.ts src/gateway/sessions-patch.test.ts`\n\nWhat regression coverage was added or updated?\n\n- Model selection tests for explicit/configured `inherit`, requester model resolution, missing requester model, and `inherit` aliases.\n- Native `spawnSubagentDirect` and `sessions_spawn` tool tests proving requester model context is forwarded and persisted.\n- Provider-qualified nested model inheritance tests for live requester context and persisted requester fallback.\n- ACP tests proving explicit `model: \"inherit\"` is rejected for ACP, aliases named `inherit` still resolve to concrete models, and configured native `subagents.model: \"inherit\"` does not become an ACP model override.\n- Prompt/tool description/docs coverage was regenerated or updated where behavior changed.\n\nWhat failed before this fix, if known?\n\nClawSweeper flagged that ACP `model: \"inherit\"` silently became `undefined` because ACP has no native requester-model inheritance context. This revision returns an explicit `runtime_policy` error for that ACP tool override instead.\n\nIf no test was added, why not?\n\nN/A; focused regression tests and docs were added or updated.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes. Native subagent model selection can now explicitly inherit the requester session model. ACP now rejects explicit `model: \"inherit\"` instead of silently falling back to the ACP harness default.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes. `agents.defaults.subagents.model` and `agents.list[].subagents.model` now document the `\"inherit\"` sentinel for native subagents while preserving aliases named `inherit`.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo direct security/auth/secret/network changes. Tool execution behavior changes only for subagent model selection when `inherit` is selected or when ACP receives an unsupported explicit inherit sentinel.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nModel precedence across native subagents, ACP runtime options, nested provider/model refs, and alias resolution.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nFocused tests cover explicit overrides, configured defaults, alias precedence, missing requester model errors, native persistence, provider-qualified nested model refs, ACP rejection, ACP alias compatibility, and sessions patch behavior. A temporary real Gateway proof also exercised `sessions.patch` plus `tools.invoke`/`sessions_spawn`.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nCI and maintainer review.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nAuthor-side changes and local proof are complete; CI/re-review is next.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nAddressed ClawSweeper's ACP `model: \"inherit\"` finding and added real Gateway `sessions_spawn` proof for provider-qualified nested model inheritance.\n",
